09/10/2009
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Thousands of people attended the funeral Thursday (October 8th) of the soccer fan who was killed in the southwest town of Siroki Brijeg ahead of a football match. Vedran Puljic, 24, was shot dead on Sunday in clashes that broke out when fans of the Sarajevo team arrived to watch the game against the local soccer squad. Fans of each team accuse the other of starting the violence. Police quickly detained the suspected killer but he escaped from custody just as quickly. Eight police officers are under arrest for allegedly helping him. (Dnevni Avaz, Fena, Nezavisne Novine, Beta, Politika - 08/10/09)
